27827.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"d4drk","text":"Mount sample onto the cryostat chuck using OCT in the desired orientation.  A flat surface can be shaved onto the mounting surface using a razor blade to ensure correct orientation and good adherence.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7upqt","text":"The angle of the stage should be adjusted to allow for a less acute passage of the tissue section over the blade as seen in the figure.  Acute angles cause the surrounding CMC to fragment and lose structural integrity.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"cia23","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"8trj3","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"572ACD30D99811E9A04E8F776A62C1BF","height":248.4389534883722,"id":48166,"is_image":true,"is_video":false,"legend":"","mime":"image/jpeg","original_name":"dave cryostat.jpg","placeholder":"","source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/public/cac5dc7b8e855a6fc7a40981e89238df7c1037e3767a5311cd299b0874b5a9c5/brbg6by6.jpg","width":406.00000000000006}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"796f3","text":"Trim CMC using larger section increments of 30-50 μm until the tissue becomes visible.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"17dr1","text":"Before procuring sections for imaging, the blade should be replaced as trimming can cause blade dulling.  This will diminish section quality.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dd66s","text":"Once the tissue is visible, excess CMC can be removed from around the sample using a precooled razor blade if necessary.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4ecrn","text":"Once a desired region for sectioning is reached, ensure the anti-roll bar is positioned appropriately.  It must not be too far towards the sample that it scrapes the tissue.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b786q","text":"Once the sectioning becomes reproducible and consistent, obtain the number of desired sections.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ft58a","text":"Manipulate each the section into position on a target surface (slide, ITO slide) using a fine tipped paint brush on the surrounding CMC material.  This prevents the contamination or disruption on the tissue.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ai6o1","text":"Once all sections are added to the slide, invert and gently press a Teflon coated slide onto the tissues to prevent wrinkles.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"2ec0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"5f1r3","text":"Flat sections thaw mount better than wrinkled sections, which thaw at different rates across the tissue.  This can cause tissues to stretch and fold, affecting the morphology and then resulting in artifacts in the imaging data.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cldf6","text":"Thaw mount the sections onto the target using heat from your gloved hand.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3hg1n","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"8banq","text":"Alternately, use a slide warmer at 20oC to expedite drying.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":37,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"9u0g8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"134ta","text":"Once mounted, the section should be air dried immediately before returning the sample to the cryostat or vacuum desiccator.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dm0b4","text":"Add subsequent serial sections to the same slide until full for 3D imaging.  Take care to record any \"lost\" sections as they will affect subsequent data reconstruction.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7a0hc","text":"Carefully remove blade from container and wipe with ethanol and a lint free wipe.  Insert blade and lock into place.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3dudu","text":"First, result files are read into R using the read_toppic(file_path = path, file_name = names) function in TopPICR, where  the \"path\" is the path to the directory containing the TopPIC PrSM files and \"names\" is a character vector specifying the PrSM files to import. This function can also be utililzed to import the MS1 feature files into a separate object.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"esufj","text":"Next, the data is further processed with the augment_annotation() and  rm_false_gene() functions to account for ambiguity in proteoform identifications","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6jq1b","text":"False discovery rate (FDR) filtering is accomplished by finding the appropriate E-value cutoff to filter the results to 1% FDR at the isoform and protein level. This is provided by the find_evalue_cutoff() and apply_evalue_cutoff() functions.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"31tjj","text":" Proteoform inference is performed with infer_pf() function and the proteoform level  is determined with set_pf_level() function . ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2jupg","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"8q0s5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"citation","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"authors":"Smith LM, Thomas PM, Shortreed MR, Schaffer LV, Fellers RT, LeDuc RD, Tucholski T, Ge Y, Agar JN, Anderson LC, Chamot-Rooke J, Gault J, Loo JA, Paša-Tolić L, Robinson CV, Schlüter H, Tsybin YO, Vilaseca M, Vizcaíno JA, Danis PO, Kelleher NL","can_edit":1,"date":"1569888000","doi":"https://doi.org/10.1038/s41592-019-0573-x","guid":"3101BF201E6D11ED861D25ECE0B6E9AF","id":1945,"journal":"Nature methods","protocol_id":"0","title":"A five-level classification system for proteoform identifications."}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dmcr0","text":"Retention time alignment is processed with the form_model() and align_rt() functions. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9sn9t","text":"Mass calibration is accomplished with the calc_error() and recalibrate_mass() functions","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2bff2","text":"Clustering and deisotoping error correction is performed with the cluster() and create_pcg() functions. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"adjb1","text":"Metadata for each proteoform cluster is generated with the create_mdata() function.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5lsm9","text":"Steps 4.5 and 4.6 are applied to the MS1 feature files as well before features are matched and combined  (for MBR) with the match_features() and combine_features() functions. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

68221.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"rek9","text":"Load DMSO as capturing media onto the microPOTS chip. Microdroplet processing in one pot for trace samples (microPOTS) chips are polyproplyene chips designed for benchtop manipulation of low sample volumes  ( \u003c 5 μL). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a3q42","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"ekhvu","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"citation","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"authors":"Xu K, Liang Y, Piehowski PD, Dou M, Schwarz KC, Zhao R, Sontag RL, Moore RJ, Zhu Y, Kelly RT","can_edit":1,"date":"1561939200","doi":"https://doi.org/10.1007/s00216-018-1493-9","guid":"1CB90EC0173C11EDBE745379E0C8D11C","id":1911,"journal":"Analytical and bioanalytical chemistry","protocol_id":"0","title":"Benchtop-compatible sample processing workflow for proteome profiling of \u003c 100 mammalian cells."}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"74juo","text":"Pipette 1 µL of DMSO onto each microPOT chip well","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"emcn7","text":"Tissue section with LCM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8q6pl","text":"Cover the chip with the glass slide and enclose with aluminum foil. Store at 4°C until ready for use.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2suom","text":"Turn on the LCM (PALM MicroBeam).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5v8p6","text":"Scan the tissue slide.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"b7167","text":"Find the target region on scanned image","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"cpsh8","text":"Navigate to the region of interest (ROI).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9p7n5","text":"Draw grid lines (1 voxel size= 2500 µm2) on ROI.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c16b9","text":"Load the laser setting (Speed 1, Cut energy 40, LPC Energy delta15).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5a2ir","text":"Load the microPOTS chip on the collector (slide collector 48). Align A1 corner of slide collector and A2 well corner of the microPOTS chip.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ed5r1","text":"Start the collection with CenterRoboLPC function.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bagjb","text":"After collecting all voxels, check on the microscope if every DMSO droplet contains the tissue voxel.\n","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d63bo","text":"Remove the microPOTS chip carefully from the collector and cover it with the glass slide.\n","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"72ers","text":"Dry DMSO from microPOTS chip","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"e4v8b","text":"Set incubator temperature to  70 °C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9800t","text":"Place uncovered chips  into incubator for 60  minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3cn3v","text":"After DMSO has evaporated, check the microPOTS chip under optical microscope to perform a QC check for missing tissue pieces. \n","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4437a","text":"Tissue protein extraction","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6emjb","text":"Set incubator to 37 °C and place microPOTS chips on ice into a biological safety cabinet (BSC)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"629f7","text":"Add 1 µL of extraction buffer (4 M Urea, 5 mM TCEP, 10% DMSO, 0.1% DDM in 50 mM ABC) to each well containing tissue.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"beu9t","text":"Place microPOTS chip with cover slide into incubator at 37 °C for 30 minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7nqj6","text":"Place the microPOTS chip into vacuum chamber and slowly introduce vacuum to evaporate remaining droplet.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"78n1k","text":"Nuclease-based histone extraction","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4bi2","text":"To each well on the microPOTS chip, add 1 µL of benzonase buffer (1 mM MgCl2 in 50 mM ABC with 2.5 unit/µL benzonase). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":75,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fo6n4","text":"Incubate microPOTS chip with cover slide at  37 °C for 60 minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"e0lk9","text":"Transferring sample for LC-MS analysis","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9seeo","text":"To an LC-MS vial, add a PCR tube with cap cut off. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5kf17","text":"Transfer 1  µL of sample from each well into a PCR-insert LC-MS vial containing 10 µL of quenching buffer. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"366ev","text":"Add 10  µL of quenching buffer (94.9% water, 4.9% MeCN, 0.2% FA) to each PCR-insert LC-MS vial.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3pt8p","text":"Re-pipette 2  µL of quenching buffer from the LC-MS vial back into the well to extract protein that may be adsorbed to the microPOTS surface. Remove the 2  µL back into the PCR-insert LC-MS vial","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"gqhj","text":"Samples are now prepared and ready for LC-MS analysis. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

description: {"blocks":[{"key":"828nn","text":"This is the overall workflow for LCMS top down proteomics of kidney functional units from tissue sections using the MicroPOTS platform. The expected outcomes are proteoform identification and quantitation values from selected tissue functional units.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
